#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:1
msgid "Introduce New vtkFrustum Implicit Function and Widget"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:3
msgid "Introduce implicit Frustum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:5
msgid ""
"The new `vtkFrustum` implicit function represents a frustum resembling a "
"pyramid with a clipped top. You can shape it by using the setters for its "
"vertical/horizontal angles, i.e. the angles between its forward axis and its "
"top and bottom, or right and left planes respectively. The distance between "
"the near plane and the frustum's origin can also be set. As for all "
"`vtkImplicitFunction`s, you can manipulate its position/orientation/scale by "
"setting a transform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:7
msgid "Add a new Implicit Frustum Widget"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:9
msgid ""
"The new `vtkFrustum` has a widget representation. The representation can be "
"manipulated through widget controls:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:10
msgid "Rotate through the orientation handles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:11
msgid "Translate through the origin or near plane center handles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:12
msgid ""
"Adjust vertical/horizontal angles through the \"far plane\" edges handles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/frustum-implicit-widget.md:13
msgid "Adjust near plane distance through the near plane edges handle."
msgstr ""

